Uses of Package
phylo3D.trees

Packages that use phylo3D.trees
phylo3D.datafiles This package contains functionality for updating the standard data files.  
phylo3D.tools This package contains the tool classes i.e. the classes with main methods called by the user.  
phylo3D.trees This package contains all the main data structure classes i.e. trees and their nodes. 
 

Classes in phylo3D.trees used by phylo3D.datafiles
TreeNCBI
          Class is data structure for the NCBI taxonomy information
 

Classes in phylo3D.trees used by phylo3D.tools
NodeData
          Abstract class representing the data in a node
TreeNCBI
          Class is data structure for the NCBI taxonomy information
TreeNH
          Class is a data structure for holding phylogenetic information that is to be output in NH format
TreeWalrus
          Class implementing functionality for printing out a LibSea format representation of TreeNCBI so that the TreeNCBI can be visualised using the hyperbolic tree visualisation program Walrus.
 

Classes in phylo3D.trees used by phylo3D.trees
NodeData
          Abstract class representing the data in a node
NodeDataNCBI
          Class representing a node in the NCBI tree of life i.e. a combination of the data from the siblingGroups table with the data from the names table.
NodeDataNH
          Class acting as a data holder for the nodes of an TreeNH.
Tree
          Class representing a Tree implemented using a Hashtable.
TreeNCBI
          Class is data structure for the NCBI taxonomy information
TreeNH
          Class is a data structure for holding phylogenetic information that is to be output in NH format
